  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria

        Concurrent Medication:

        Allowed:

          -  Zidovudine (AZT).

        Exclusion Criteria

        Co-existing Condition:

        Patients with the following are excluded:

          -  Active opportunistic infection or progressive Kaposi's sarcoma (KS).

          -  Dementia.

          -  Lymphoma.

        Concurrent Medication:

        Excluded within 3 weeks of study entry:

          -  Other experimental AIDS therapy.

        Patients with the following are excluded:

          -  Active opportunistic infection or progressive Kaposi's sarcoma (KS).

        Patients must be either HIV seropositive or have AIDS or AIDS related complex (ARC) and
        have life expectancy of at least 6 months.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
